What is a Constructor in JavaScript?
A constructor in JavaScript is a special function used to create and initialize objects. 
It acts as a blueprint for creating multiple objects with the same properties and methods.

class Person {
    constructor(name, age) {
        this.name = name;
        this.age = age;
    }

    sayHello() {
        console.log(`Hi, I'm ${this.name} and I'm ${this.age} years old.`);
    }
}

// Creating objects using the class constructor
const person1 = new Person("Alice", 25);
person1.sayHello(); // Hi, I'm Alice and I'm 25 years old.
